relevant_findings.abdominal_examination: Soft, tender to palpation most in RUQ and epigastric area, no rebound/guarding, equivocal clinical Murphy's sign, no edema

relevant_findings.ultrasound: Liver mildly echogenic suggestive of fatty infiltration. Gallbladder mildly distended with numerous layering gallstones and sludge. No focal lesions or biliary duct dilatation.
